{"url": "https://www.reddit.com/r/learnprogramming/comments/9azjxl/i_need_help_with_this_code_javascript_and_html/", "text": "Hi I made a code that when you press a button it asks you wether you did like the image or not. I want to make 2 if statements and 1 else one. i want to make it so it doesnt say Danke! and then du bist boese! Please help me with the code here is the code:\n\n      var Frage = prompt(\"Ja oder Nein?\");\n      if (Frage==\"Ja\"){\n        alert(\"Danke!\");\n      }\n        if (Frage==\"ja\"){\n          alert(\"Danke!\");\n        }\n          else {\n            alert(\"Du bist boese!!!!\");\n          }\n    }\n\n\u200b", "score": 2, "comments": [{"body": "In this code if \"Ja\" is entered instead of \"ja\" you are going to get both responses. This is because there is 2 if blocks in this code instead of just one. There are 2 ways to fix this, use an else if block or use toLowerCase().\n\nelse if: \n\n    var Frage = prompt(\"Ja oder Nein?\");\n    if (Frage==\"Ja\"){\n        alert(\"Danke!\");\n    }\n    else if (Frage==\"ja\"){\n      alert(\"Danke!\");\n    }\n    else {\n        alert(\"Du bist boese!!!!\");\n    }\n\nUsing an else if like this will make sure that only one of the code blocks is run\n\n[toLowerCase()](https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/jsref_tolowercase.asp)\n\n    if (Frage.toLowerCase() == \"ja\") {\n        alert(\"Danke!\");\n    } else {\n        alert(\"Du bist boese!!!!\");\n    }\n\nThis way you don't need to repeat yourself and more varieties will trigger the \"Danke\" alert", "id": "e4z7tee", "replies": [{"body": "Thank you", "id": "e4z822l", "replies": []}]}], "title": "I need help with this code javascript and html"}